  "module_title": "System Administration",
  "summary": "System Administration provides centralized management of scheduled jobs, global feature flags, code lists, custom data tables, and audit trails for the application.",
  "where_it_fits": "This module is an administrative area exposed via the top navigation (Admin) and appears in the content area with breadcrumbs and icon-based sidebar context; it is used for system-wide configuration and background job lifecycle management across the application. It sits at the platform-level configuration layer, affecting Clients, Accounts, Products and reporting behaviors referenced elsewhere in the app.",
  "assumed_state_on_entry": "Logged in as a user with administrative privileges (role permitting access to Admin/System Administration) and viewing the Admin section in the top navigation."
